President Joe Biden gave a speech at an event honoring teachers. He expressed gratitude for educators and highlighted their importance in shaping the future. He also emphasized the need to invest in education to keep up with other countries. Biden shared a personal story about his own journey in politics and how teachers played a role in his confidence and success. He thanked the teachers present and acknowledged the impact they have on students. The President also gave two teachers gifts and briefly addressed a question about Colin Powell's COVID-19 vaccination status, urging Americans to continue getting vaccinated.